    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is structured as a task-oriented, single-page dashboard. It maintains the 3 "missions" from the source guide as thematic sections for a clear user flow. This structure was chosen over a simple text-to-webpage conversion to transform a passive guide into an active workshop. The flow is: Header -> Sticky Navigation -> Mission 1 (Interactive Info Cards) -> Mission 2 (Live Password Checker) -> Mission 3 (Interactive Privacy Audit Simulator + Data Viz) -> Final Checklist -> Footer. This task-based structure allows users to directly engage with each concept, providing immediate feedback and a safe practice environment, thus enhancing learning and retention. A sticky navigation bar is included for easy movement between these interactive tasks. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Mission 1 (Huella Digital): Goal: Inform/Organize. Method: Interactive Cards (HTML/CSS/JS). Interaction: On-click info reveals. Justification: More engaging than a static list of concepts.
        - Mission 2 (Contraseñas): Goal: Compare/Inform. Method: Real-time Password Strength Meter (HTML/CSS/JS). Interaction: Input field with a dynamically updating progress bar and text feedback. Justification: Provides instant, tangible feedback, making the concept of password strength concrete. Superior to linking to an external site.
        - Mission 3 (Privacidad): Goal: Organize/Inform. Method: Donut Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) and an Interactive Settings Simulator (HTML/CSS/JS). Interaction: Chart visualizes data; simulator allows clicking through a mock UI. Justification: The chart provides a quick data insight, while the simulator makes the abstract process of revoking permissions easy to understand in a safe, guided way.
        - Checklist: Goal: Organize. Method: Interactive Checklist (HTML/CSS/JS). Justification: Provides a sense of completion and reinforces the key actions.
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
